        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued November 24 at 8:25AM CST by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 825 AM CST, Doppler radar was tracking a line of strong
thunderstorms extending from near Dierks to over Lodi, or extending
from near Dierks to 17 miles southwest of Atlanta, moving east at 45
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Texarkana, Hope, Atlanta, Wake Village, Ashdown, Nashville,
Stamps, Lewisville, Mineral Springs, Dierks, Vivian, Nash, Hooks,
Linden, Queen City, Redwater, Plain Dealing, Red Lick and Fouke.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
